<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Dalain on 04-03-2001 05:10 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">This is my personal opinion.

Scenario A is bogus.  Again my opinion, but using some alt that's way too low a level and claiming "camping" is wrong.  Be it some 30th lvl druid, or some lowish lvl monk or whatever.  I just personally don't buy that at all.  I especially don't by it if Fire giants are up.  FG's should be dead on spawn if somebody is "camping" ragefire.

Scenario B is a bit tougher.  If there is a group capable of killing FGs, which now adays can be done with a pretty small number of people, but lets say it's 1 group.  If the cleric is there with them, again another thing about me is somebody else doesn't camp something for you, then I personally would say that they were camping ragefire.  The tough part is how long to give that person to get the forces required to kill him.  I suppose personally I would inquire to the person how long they thought it would be before the help came.  I don't know that I would have any set amount of time I'd give them.  But personally, if they spent X amount of time, clearing fire giants and waiting for him to spawn, to me, it gives them alot more rights to it then people that just show up, after it spawns, with the required forces to do it.  Again, that's just me.  But the important difference from A to B to me is that the cleric must be present, and the group should be clearing the FG's as they spawn.  

*shrug*

We've had some problems on my server with people trying to do something like scenario A.  Personally, I'm very glad that I got mine when I did, back when overking was tough and there wasn't very many people at the zordak stage.  People would just kill FGs if they were up, and if they found Zordak, you killed him.

Dalain

